    },
    "notes": [
      "Layout traced from front-on Crypto Museum photograph. Positions are logical (row/col grid), not pixel-exact. Pixel-perfect placement is deferred to Phase 4 rendering (see SPEC Appendix A §4.3).",
      "Manual Appendix F states 'Standard QWERTY plus 15 special function keys with no shifted functions.' Our count: 26 alpha + 10 digit + 8 punctuation/space + 15 special = 59 keys. Matches spec total despite spec row-5 layout being fabricated.",
      "Key id is the canonical name used in code; legend is the glyph rendered on the cap. Unicode arrows (↑ ↓ ← →) are used as legends; code names are UP/DOWN/LEFT/RIGHT.",
      "ENTER is a tall key spanning rows 2 and 3 on the right edge (rowSpan: 2).",
      "SRCH doubles as the power-ON key when unit is off — there is no separate power switch (MANUAL p.8: 'The unit is turned on by pressing the SRCH key')."
    ],
    "rowCount": 5,
    "keyCount": 59,
    "categories": {
      "alpha": "A-Z letter keys",
      "digit": "0-9 number keys",
      "punct": "visible punctuation and space",
      "nav": "cursor movement and buffer navigation",
      "edit": "delete and structural editing",
      "special": "top-level function keys: ZRO, XIT, CLK, SRCH, ENTER"
    }
  },

